OL,3,CChemical company fined #2.5 million
OL,4,Cfor releasing corrosive acids into the
OL,5,Cair
OL,7,FAnother investigation by HSE into the
OL,8,Frelease of sulphuric acid in August
OL,9,F2020, identified a lack of inspection
OL,10,Fand maintenance of the pipework and
OL,11,Fvalves. According to HSE, the leak
OL,12,Fcontinued for a further two days due
OL,13,Fto the inability to operate a manual
OL,14,Fvalve to stop the process. No one was
OL,15,Fharmed.
OL,17,FIndustrial Chemicals Ltd pleaded
OL,18,Fguilty following the incidents in 2020
OL,19,Fand was in total fined # 2.5 million.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
